    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "`forge inspect` will print the storage layout as outputted by the compiler, but I think the scope of this issue might be for a more user friendly display similar to slither's printer? Maybe we add a `--table` or `--pretty` option to `forge inspect` and for `mode`s that support it we display a more human-friendly format. Potential storage layout pretty print:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ forge inspect <contract> storage-layout --pretty\r\n+----------+---------+-------+--------+\r\n|     Name |   Type  | Slot  | Offset |\r\n+----------+---------+-------+--------+\r\n| varA     | uint256 | 0     | 0      |\r\n| varB     | uint256 | 1     | 0      |\r\n+----------+---------+-------+--------+\r\n```",
